			)
		)
		(uuid "f8000194-a4f2-4d14-a4e6-494a83dcc296")
	)
	(text_box "Hex Extender Cable\n\nThis is an USB hub and USB-C plug extension cable for the hex master circuit.\n\nThe input plug is meant to plug into the master circuit and this cable circuit\nincludes a 4-way USB hub followed by 4 USB-C connectors that plug into downstream\nhex motor drivers.\n\nPower is supplied as a folded over FPC connector."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 33.02 30.0394 0)
		(size 110.49 34.7306)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.5 1.5)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "1f2cd93c-8b7e-4e68-aa3b-015869c6a291")
	)
	(text_box "Servo connectors with USB-C and power via FPC\n\nEach hierarchical component represents a pair of USB-C and FPC connectors\nfor a downstream device.\n\nThe NRST and BOOT0 wires can be connected either way and also double\nas I2C connectors for further multiplexing downstream devices. We\nneed to connect them to the GPIO and I2C multiplexers. They will have\nthe following options:\n	1. The STM32 servo drivers will have a pull-up on NRST and pull-down on BOOT0.\n	We will use the GPIO multiplexer to first read the values to determine the plug\n	orientation then we can toggle the lines to enter the bootloader mode to upload\n	code without the device ever being programmed.\n	2. If both lines are pulled up then we have connected a downstream multiplexer.\n	Test out which way the connection works by attempting an I2C transaction; note\n	send some blank data in order to reset the data lines if we have guessed wrong.\n	3. If both lines are pulled down, then it's probably not our device."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 180.34 106.8476 0)
		(size 107.95 36.6624)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "64ee41d2-56b2-475c-bcd8-6734f041c47e")
	)
